<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Applications">Applications</span><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DMatrix_calculus&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D27" title=3D"Edit section: Applications">edit</=
a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Matrix differential calculus is used in statistics, particularly for the=
 statistical analysis of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multivari=
ate_distribution" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Multivariate distribution"=
>multivariate distributions</a>, especially the <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Multivariate_normal_distribution" title=3D"Multivariate norma=
l distribution">multivariate normal distribution</a> and other <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elliptical_distribution" title=3D"Elliptical d=
istribution">elliptical distributions</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_calculus#cite_no=
te-11">[11]</a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_calculus#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Matrix_calculus#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup>
</p><p>It is used in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regression_an=
alysis" title=3D"Regression analysis">regression analysis</a> to compute, f=
or example, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_least_squar=
es_(mathematics)#The_general_problem" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Linear=
 least squares (mathematics)">ordinary least squares regression formula</a>=
 for the case of multiple <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Explanat=
ory_variable" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Explanatory variable">explanat=
ory variables</a>.
</p>
